\begin_layout Subsection
construct quality measure
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
对于任意给定的变量x，首先将其转换为排序值：
\begin_inset Formula $r_{i}=rank(x_{i})$
\end_inset

，再计算相应的z-score：
\begin_inset Formula $z_{x}=\frac{(r-\mu_{r})}{\sigma_{r}}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
profitability: gross profits over assets (GPOA), return on equity (ROE),
 return on assets (ROA), cash flow over assets (CFOA), gross margin (GMAR),
 and the fraction of earnings composed of cash (i.e.
 minus accruals, ACC).
 Then profitability score is the average of the individual z-scores:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Profitability=mean(z_{GPOA}+z_{ROE}+z_{ROA}+z_{CFOA}+z_{GMAR}+z_{ACC})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
growth: Similarly, we measure growth as the five-year growth in profitability
 (excluding accruals), averaged across five measures:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Growth=mean(z_{\Delta GPOA}+z_{\Delta ROE}+z_{\Delta ROA}+z_{\Delta CFOA}+z_{\Delta GMAR})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
safety: We define safe securities as companies with low beta (BAB), low
 leverage (LEV), low bankruptcy risk (O-Score and Z-Score) and low ROE volatilit
y (EVOL)
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Safety=mean(z_{BAB}+z_{LEV}+z_{O-Score}+z_{Z-Score}+z_{EVOL})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Finally, we combine the three measures into a single quality score:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Quality=aggregate(Profitability+Growth+Safety)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

